### A note for fast finishers
If you want to go further: try computing the Dirichlet energy $\mathcal{E}(H) = \frac{1}{2}\sum_{i,j} A_{ij}\|h_i - h_j\|^2$ at each layer in Q4 and plot it against $K$ — you should see it shrink with depth, which is the quantitative signature of over-smoothing. This is optional and not graded.
